# buids multiplication tabel
def multiplication_table(n):
    table = []
    for i in range(1, n + 1):
        row = []
        for j in range(1, n):
            row.append(i * j)
        table.append(row)
    return table
The outer loop goes through each row number i, and the inner loop multiplies i by each column number to fill that row, then the row gets added to the table.
